dct_title_s: Crete / compiled by the Geographical Section, General Staff, War Office ; drawn at the Ordnance Survey Office.
dct_description_sm: Relief shown by contours at 200-meter vertical intervals and spot heights. Map shows motor roads, car and mule tracks, provincial boundaries, and lighthouses. Map includes: "Grid Convergence Diagram" and "Magnetic Variation Diagram (Referred to true north) (1942)." Includes table: "To give a grid reference on this sheet." "For use by War and Navy Department Agencies only. Not for sale or distribution." Prime meridian 25° East of Greenwich. "Army Map Service. U.S. Army. Washington, D.C., 115982." / "Reprint 1943." Map has military grid.
dct_creator_sm: Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section
dct_publisher_sm: [London] : War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section, 1941.
Compiled by the Geographical Section, General Staff, War Office, 1940.
Drawn at the Ordnance Survey Office, 1941.
